<br>
Find a group of the appropriate level in an appropriate zone.  For instance: level 29-34 in the front of Split Paw.<br>
<br>
Event #1<br>
Occupy a Gnoll, buff him a couple levels, name him Gragnor Mal and put a semi-decent item on him for that level (Gnoll Hide Tome, etc.) and run over to them and say, 'It's time someone rid this place of you, Soandso,' and proceed to lay about you jumping on the cleric and stuff they aren't used to, but letting them kill you eventually.  Then you leave.<br>
<br>
Event #2<br>
Or, you put a FS Dagger on a deeper mob and you load up a human model and say to the group, 'The Gnoll on the bridge has a dagger that belonged to my father.  Return it to me, and I'll reward you with 100 pp' (or whatever).  Once they get the reward, you leave.<br>
<br>
I could make up ten of these over lunch and do each in about half an hour.  I would write them down and, as a matter of fact, repeat them.  Maybe once every two weeks or so, once I had a stable of 30 or 40 events.   Short events = no PC mobbing.  You check out the zone first, if the right PCs are in place, you do something.  If some level 54 Druid is PLing some 24 Monk, you move on.  You reward out of the way people in small ways that they remember.<br>
